WEBVTT

00:02.569 --> 00:04.570
<i>In last week's episode of</i> Soap,

00:04.571 --> 00:07.072
<i>Carol told Jodie she's pregnant</i>
<i>and he's the father,</i>

00:07.073 --> 00:10.075
<i>presenting Jodie with a problem</i>
<i>that won't disappear.</i>

00:10.076 --> 00:12.077
<i>Because Elaine's father</i>
<i>cut her off,</i>

00:12.078 --> 00:13.579
<i>her inheritance disappeared,</i>

00:13.580 --> 00:16.081
<i>so Elaine and Danny had</i>
<i>to move in with Burt and Mary,</i>

00:16.082 --> 00:18.584
<i>who wish she'd disappear.</i>

00:18.585 --> 00:20.085
<i>Tim and Corinne</i>
<i>are going to be married,</i>

00:20.086 --> 00:23.589
<i>and Tim's mother wishes</i>
<i>Corinne would disappear.</i>

00:23.590 --> 00:26.091
<i>Chester and Dutch</i>
<i>disappeared from prison</i>

00:26.092 --> 00:28.093
<i>and had the police</i>
<i>looking for them.</i>

00:28.094 --> 00:30.095
<i>Benson, Billy, Eunice,</i>
<i>and Corinne</i>

00:30.096 --> 00:31.096
<i>disappeared from the dining room</i>

00:31.097 --> 00:33.098
<i>and had Jessica</i>
<i>looking for them.</i>

00:33.099 --> 00:35.601
<i>Then Jessica disappeared.</i>

00:35.602 --> 00:36.602
<i>Confused?</i>

00:36.603 --> 00:38.605
<i>You won't be</i>
<i>after this week's episode of...</i>

00:44.611 --> 00:46.612
<i>This is the story</i>
<i>of two sisters,</i>

00:46.613 --> 00:49.114
<i>Jessica Tate</i>

00:49.115 --> 00:51.116
<i>and Mary Campbell.</i>

00:51.117 --> 00:54.620
<i>These are the Tates...</i>

00:54.621 --> 00:58.624
<i>and these are the Campbells.</i>

00:58.625 --> 01:00.627
<i>And this is</i> Soap.

01:03.630 --> 01:05.632
[♪]

01:08.134 --> 01:10.136
[SHOUTING]

01:12.000 --> 01:18.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:30.657 --> 01:32.157
All right, Mrs. Tate,

01:32.158 --> 01:34.159
you scream for help,
and I'll blow your head off.

01:34.160 --> 01:36.161
Do as he says, Jess.

01:36.162 --> 01:37.663
Chester?

01:37.664 --> 01:39.665
Is that you, Chester?

01:39.666 --> 01:41.667
Oh, darling, darling,

01:41.668 --> 01:43.168
you did escape.

01:43.169 --> 01:45.170
That's right,
and we're hiding out here.

01:45.171 --> 01:46.171
Now, all of you

01:46.172 --> 01:48.173
just go about doing
whatever it is you do,

01:48.174 --> 01:51.176
and remember, one word of this,
and somebody gets killed.

01:51.177 --> 01:54.680
Oh, don't be silly,

01:54.681 --> 01:56.682
but you don't have
to hide down here.

01:56.683 --> 01:59.184
We have a perfectly lovely
guest room upstairs,

01:59.185 --> 02:02.187
with a private bath.

02:02.188 --> 02:03.689
Jess, we've escaped.

02:03.690 --> 02:04.690
We have to hide.

02:04.691 --> 02:07.693
Okay, everybody, get up.

02:07.694 --> 02:08.693
Now, all of you

02:08.695 --> 02:11.196
just go about your lives
as if nothing was going on.

02:11.197 --> 02:13.699
Fine, I'll go get dessert.

02:13.700 --> 02:15.200
You hold it right there.

02:15.201 --> 02:17.703
Okay, now, everybody,

02:17.704 --> 02:20.706
you're all to live
perfectly normal lives.

02:20.707 --> 02:23.208
Sure, a normal life
with a gun up my nose?

02:23.209 --> 02:25.210
Billy, don't be rude.

02:25.211 --> 02:27.713
After all, Butch is our guest.

02:27.714 --> 02:28.714
I'm Dutch.

02:28.715 --> 02:30.215
Dutch?

02:30.216 --> 02:31.717
Hold it right there,

02:31.718 --> 02:33.219
buster.

02:34.721 --> 02:38.724
No, you fool, this man is Dutch.

02:38.725 --> 02:40.226
The Dutch are on our side.

02:45.231 --> 02:47.733
I'm very sorry, captain.

02:47.734 --> 02:49.235
Get over there.

02:51.738 --> 02:53.238
Okay, now,

02:53.239 --> 02:54.740
remember, one word...

02:54.741 --> 02:57.242
one word from anybody,

02:57.243 --> 02:58.243
and he dies.

02:58.244 --> 03:00.246
Anything in particular
we'd have to say?

03:12.258 --> 03:14.760
Uh, it's a great meal, darling.

03:14.761 --> 03:16.262
It's really
just a wonderful dinner.

03:18.765 --> 03:20.265
[SPITS]

03:20.266 --> 03:21.767
This stuffing's the pits.

03:21.768 --> 03:22.768
I'll kill her.

03:22.769 --> 03:23.769
I swear, I'll kill her.

03:23.770 --> 03:24.770
Easy, now, Mary, Mary, Mary.

03:24.771 --> 03:26.271
Come on, now.

03:26.272 --> 03:28.774
So we didn't know that Elaine
doesn't like stuffing.

03:28.775 --> 03:29.775
She's probably allergic to it

03:29.776 --> 03:31.276
and had a reaction.

03:31.277 --> 03:32.277
Just...

03:33.780 --> 03:35.782
Elaine, please.

03:40.787 --> 03:42.288
Have a nice day today, darling?

03:46.292 --> 03:47.292
Darling?

03:47.293 --> 03:48.293
[CLINKING]

03:48.294 --> 03:49.795
Nice day?

03:49.796 --> 03:51.797
It was okay.

03:51.798 --> 03:53.298
Come on, Elaine,

03:53.299 --> 03:55.300
my mother worked hard
on this meal.

03:55.301 --> 03:57.302
I'd rather starve to death.

03:57.303 --> 03:59.805
Why don't you? You could stand
to lose a few pounds.

04:01.307 --> 04:02.307
Let go of me.

04:02.308 --> 04:03.809
Hey, she didn't mean it, Elaine.

04:03.810 --> 04:04.810
She didn't mean it.

04:04.811 --> 04:05.812
I meant it.

04:07.814 --> 04:09.315
Take it easy.

04:10.817 --> 04:12.317
How was work today, darling?

04:12.318 --> 04:14.820
[VOICE SQUEAKING]
Oh, it's... the usual.

04:14.821 --> 04:17.322
Let's go out for dinner.

04:17.322 --> 04:18.322
Elaine,

04:18.324 --> 04:19.324
the way you've been
spending dough,

04:19.325 --> 04:20.826
I can't afford it.

04:20.827 --> 04:21.827
You can't afford it?

04:21.827 --> 04:22.828
You can't afford anything.

04:22.829 --> 04:24.329
That's because
you've got the brain

04:24.330 --> 04:27.332
of a flea.

04:27.333 --> 04:28.333
Okay.

04:28.334 --> 04:31.337
Danny, Danny, Danny, Danny!

04:33.840 --> 04:34.840
She's a girl.

04:34.841 --> 04:36.843
Easy, fellow.

04:39.846 --> 04:42.347
So...

04:42.348 --> 04:43.849
how do you two guys
like working together?

04:43.850 --> 04:45.851
Oh, it's terrific.
Great.

04:45.852 --> 04:47.352
Sure, one's got a flea brain,

04:47.353 --> 04:48.854
and the invisible man's
got none at all.

04:48.855 --> 04:50.857
[LETS OUT A WHOOP]

04:52.859 --> 04:54.359
Easy, easy.

04:54.360 --> 04:57.863
Darling, she's a girl.

04:57.864 --> 04:59.866
[SQUEALS]

05:07.373 --> 05:08.373
You through with that?

05:08.374 --> 05:10.376
Uh-huh...

05:14.881 --> 05:16.381
Uh...

05:16.382 --> 05:17.883
Why don't we just have
some dessert.

05:19.886 --> 05:22.888
It's your favorite, Danny:
chocolate cream pie.

05:22.889 --> 05:25.391
Oh, God, I hope
there's a stomach pump handy.

05:28.895 --> 05:30.896
Take it easy, boys.

05:30.897 --> 05:34.399
Come on, now, we're adults,

05:34.400 --> 05:35.400
and for the time being,

05:35.401 --> 05:36.401
the four of us

05:36.402 --> 05:37.903
are sharing this house together.

05:37.904 --> 05:39.905
We have to learn
to live together.

05:39.906 --> 05:42.407
We have to have respect
for each other.

05:42.408 --> 05:43.909
We're adults.

05:43.910 --> 05:44.911
Sit down.

05:47.914 --> 05:49.414
We really need that.

05:49.415 --> 05:50.916
Why don't you just apply it

05:50.917 --> 05:52.918
directly to your hips?

05:52.919 --> 05:54.921
[LAUGHING]

05:58.424 --> 06:00.426
It's not for me, dear.
It's for you.

06:30.456 --> 06:31.957
[GASPS]

06:31.958 --> 06:32.958
What are you doing here?

06:32.959 --> 06:34.960
I don't know.

06:34.961 --> 06:36.461
You came
all the way up those stairs,

06:36.462 --> 06:37.963
and you don't know why?

06:37.964 --> 06:40.465
Maybe I came up here
because I like to look at you.

06:40.466 --> 06:41.466
To look at me?

06:41.467 --> 06:43.468
Yeah, you're pretty.
No, I'm not pretty.

06:43.469 --> 06:44.970
Sure you are.
No, I'm not.

06:46.973 --> 06:48.473
Hey, you're very pretty.

06:48.474 --> 06:50.976
Listen, you,

06:50.977 --> 06:52.978
if you came up here
intending to rape me,

06:52.979 --> 06:53.979
let me tell you right now

06:53.980 --> 06:55.981
it's not going to be
any fun at all,

06:55.982 --> 06:57.482
because I'll spit in your face.

06:57.483 --> 06:58.984
I'll scratch
your eyes out. Hey, hey.

06:58.985 --> 07:00.485
I'll kill you
before I let you... Hey...

07:00.486 --> 07:01.987
Yeah, what?

07:01.988 --> 07:04.990
I happen to be a killer,
not a rapist.

07:04.991 --> 07:09.494
Oh, I love it.
A killer looks down on a rapist.

07:09.495 --> 07:10.996
And if I was a rapist,

07:10.997 --> 07:12.999
let me tell you something,
I wouldn't rape you...

07:14.000 --> 07:15.000
But I'm not a rapist.

07:15.001 --> 07:19.004
Oh, and how come
you wouldn't rape me?

07:19.005 --> 07:20.005
Because I'm not pretty?

07:20.006 --> 07:23.508
No, you are pretty.
You're very pretty.

07:23.509 --> 07:25.010
Why would you think
that you're not pretty?

07:25.011 --> 07:26.511
Because
when I was a little girl,

07:26.512 --> 07:29.014
I was fat and I had buck teeth.

07:29.015 --> 07:30.096
I looked like a blowfish...

07:32.018 --> 07:33.518
And it doesn't matter
what anyone says

07:33.519 --> 07:35.020
or how I look or what I do.

07:35.021 --> 07:36.521
I still feel like

07:36.522 --> 07:38.023
a fat little funny-looking
7-year-old girl.

07:38.024 --> 07:39.524
That's funny.

07:39.525 --> 07:40.525
That's not a bit funny.

07:40.526 --> 07:42.527
No, but that's how I feel.

07:42.528 --> 07:45.530
Like a fat little
7-year-old girl?

07:45.531 --> 07:49.534
No, like a puny, little,
skinny little 9-year-old.

07:49.535 --> 07:51.036
You see, when I was a kid,

07:51.037 --> 07:53.038
I had
all these terrible allergies.

07:53.039 --> 07:55.040
I had asthma and
hayfever and hives.

07:55.041 --> 07:56.541
You name it,
I was allergic to it.

07:56.542 --> 07:59.544
I spent my whole childhood
just trying to get a breath,

07:59.545 --> 08:01.046
and I was
real sickly looking too.

08:01.047 --> 08:03.548
The kids used to call me Worm
and beat me up.

08:03.549 --> 08:05.050
Oh...

08:05.051 --> 08:08.053
When I was 11,
I changed my name to Dutch.

08:08.054 --> 08:10.555
They still called me Worm.
It used to make me so mad.

08:10.556 --> 08:13.058
And so you became a killer.

08:13.059 --> 08:16.061
What are you, crazy?
I was 11.

08:16.062 --> 08:18.063
Oh, yeah.

08:18.064 --> 08:19.064
Worm...

08:19.065 --> 08:21.566
Can you imagine that,
being called Worm?

08:21.567 --> 08:24.569
Well, listen, they used
to call me Butterball.

08:24.570 --> 08:26.571
[CHUCKLES]

08:26.572 --> 08:27.572
They called you Butterball?
Mm-hmm.

08:27.573 --> 08:30.075
Everyone except Corinne.

08:30.076 --> 08:32.078
She used to call me Lardo.

08:34.080 --> 08:35.580
Butterball...

08:35.581 --> 08:37.082
[LAUGHS]

08:37.082 --> 08:38.582
I think that's kind of cute.

08:38.583 --> 08:40.585
That is not a bit cute.

08:40.586 --> 08:41.586
[LAUGHS]

08:41.587 --> 08:44.089
How you doing, Butterball?

08:44.090 --> 08:45.591
Knock it off, Worm.

08:51.597 --> 08:53.598
I can't believe I'm sitting here

08:53.599 --> 08:56.101
laughing with a killer.

08:56.102 --> 08:57.602
I can't believe I'm sitting here

08:57.603 --> 09:00.605
laughing with a rich girl.

09:00.606 --> 09:03.608
Well... You're really very nice.

09:03.609 --> 09:04.610
So are you...

09:06.112 --> 09:07.112
And you're very pretty.

09:07.113 --> 09:08.613
No.

09:08.614 --> 09:11.116
It's too bad I'm not a rapist.

09:18.124 --> 09:19.124
Oh, Burt.

09:19.125 --> 09:20.625
I know, Mary, I know.

09:20.626 --> 09:21.626
Three meals a day.

09:21.627 --> 09:22.627
I know.

09:22.628 --> 09:24.629
That's 21 meals a week.

09:24.630 --> 09:25.630
I know, Mary.

09:25.631 --> 09:28.133
I wonder how many meals a year
that is.

09:28.134 --> 09:31.137
1092.

09:34.140 --> 09:35.641
BOB: Chuck.

09:37.643 --> 09:39.644
BOB: Chuck!

09:39.645 --> 09:41.146
Bob, I have a date.

09:41.147 --> 09:43.148
Now, go back to bed
and don't wait up, okay?

09:43.149 --> 09:44.149
I'm going with you.

09:44.150 --> 09:45.650
You're not going.
Yes, I am.

09:45.651 --> 09:47.152
Look, Bob. Wait a minute, Bob.

09:47.153 --> 09:48.653
No more.

09:48.654 --> 09:50.155
We have been through this
how many times?

09:50.156 --> 09:51.156
You know what I think?

09:51.157 --> 09:53.658
I think it stinks,
that's what I think.

09:53.659 --> 09:55.160
Come on, Bob.

09:55.161 --> 09:56.161
Now, look,

09:56.162 --> 09:58.163
if you had the date,
I wouldn't go with you.

09:58.164 --> 10:00.165
I mean, I just want
to be alone with her.

10:00.166 --> 10:02.167
You'll be alone.
I won't say a word.

10:02.168 --> 10:03.668
I just want to see the movie.

10:03.669 --> 10:05.670
Gee, I got all dressed up
and everything.

10:05.671 --> 10:09.174
Chuck, Chuck, go. I can babysit.

10:09.175 --> 10:10.675
Hey, thanks, Dad.

10:10.676 --> 10:12.177
Yeah, okay, fine, fine,

10:12.178 --> 10:13.678
don't take me
with you tonight...

10:13.679 --> 10:14.679
Yeah, yeah.

10:14.680 --> 10:15.680
And I don't go with you

10:15.681 --> 10:16.681
to the audition tomorrow.

10:16.682 --> 10:18.183
Come on, Bob.

10:18.184 --> 10:20.185
I mean, that could be
a big break for us.

10:20.186 --> 10:23.189
No, you want to be alone.

10:24.690 --> 10:26.191
Well, you can be
alone there too.

10:26.192 --> 10:27.192
We'll just see

10:27.193 --> 10:28.694
how your career takes off.

10:34.700 --> 10:36.701
Okay, okay, okay, you can come.

10:36.702 --> 10:37.702
Yeah?

10:37.703 --> 10:40.706
Yeah, but this time,
keep your hands off her.

10:45.211 --> 10:46.711
Burt,

10:46.712 --> 10:51.716
do you think Chuck might need
some professional help?

10:51.717 --> 10:54.719
No, no, no, no, no,

10:54.720 --> 10:56.721
I just think
he's got to discipline Bob more.

10:56.722 --> 10:57.723
That's all.

11:02.228 --> 11:03.728
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

11:03.729 --> 11:06.231
Oh, my God, they're back.

11:06.232 --> 11:09.234
Oh, Jodie.
How you doing, fellow?

11:09.235 --> 11:10.735
Fine, great. Hiya, Ma.

11:10.736 --> 11:13.238
Hello, honey.
How are you?

11:13.239 --> 11:15.240
Fine, terrific,
never felt better in my life.

11:15.241 --> 11:17.742
You know, I felt so good,
I had to drive up and say hello.

11:17.743 --> 11:18.743
You've got a problem.

11:18.744 --> 11:20.245
Boy, do I have a problem.

11:21.747 --> 11:24.249
Well... you know,
you two guys talk, you know...

11:24.250 --> 11:25.750
No, Burt, it's okay,
you can stay,

11:25.751 --> 11:27.252
but please, no cracks, huh?

11:27.253 --> 11:28.254
I mean, this is serious.

11:35.761 --> 11:36.761
What is it?

11:36.762 --> 11:38.263
Carol's pregnant,
and I'm the father.

11:39.265 --> 11:40.765
[STIFLED WHOOP]

11:40.766 --> 11:42.267
[CHEERING]

11:46.772 --> 11:48.774
I knew it, I knew it!

11:50.776 --> 11:52.277
I knew he wasn't a pansy.

11:52.278 --> 11:54.279
Look at this guy now.
Look at him!

11:54.280 --> 11:57.282
Burt,
this doesn't mean I'm not gay.

11:57.283 --> 11:59.784
Jodie, please, what it means is

11:59.785 --> 12:01.786
you're good at it.

12:01.787 --> 12:03.788
The first time, she's pregnant.

12:03.789 --> 12:05.290
It's beginner's luck.

12:05.291 --> 12:08.793
How about this man?
Look at him here.

12:08.794 --> 12:10.795
Mary, he made a girl pregnant.

12:10.796 --> 12:12.297
Well, I must say,

12:12.298 --> 12:15.300
it wasn't something
I expected from you.

12:15.301 --> 12:17.802
From Danny, yes, but you...

12:17.803 --> 12:18.803
Yeah, I know,

12:18.804 --> 12:20.805
but I don't know
what to do about it.

12:20.806 --> 12:22.307
You just do it a few more times,

12:22.308 --> 12:23.308
you'll be hooked.

12:23.309 --> 12:24.810
It's like pretzels.

12:30.316 --> 12:33.318
Burt, this is serious.

12:33.319 --> 12:37.322
Burt, Carol is pregnant.
I'm in love with Dennis.

12:37.323 --> 12:38.324
Aww...

12:39.825 --> 12:41.826
This is not the perfect match.
I mean...

12:41.827 --> 12:44.329
Mom, what do I do?

12:44.330 --> 12:47.832
I don't know what to tell you.

12:47.833 --> 12:51.336
I mean, when you were 6,
and you came home from day camp

12:51.337 --> 12:53.838
because Perry Miller
was splashing you,

12:53.839 --> 12:55.340
I could say, "Splash back,"

12:55.341 --> 12:57.342
but this...

12:57.343 --> 13:01.347
How can I tell you how to spend
the rest of your life?

13:02.848 --> 13:05.350
I have no frame of reference
for this.

13:05.351 --> 13:06.851
I know.

13:06.852 --> 13:08.853
There are not a lot of books
written on the subject.

13:08.854 --> 13:10.355
Who'd want to read them?

13:10.356 --> 13:12.858
I'm going to get some coffee.

13:14.860 --> 13:16.361
Oh, Jodie, I'm sorry.

13:16.362 --> 13:18.863
I don't mean to let you down.
I love you.

13:18.864 --> 13:20.365
I wish I had an answer.

13:20.366 --> 13:22.867
It's okay, Ma,
really, it's okay,

13:22.868 --> 13:25.870
and your answers
aren't so hot anyway, lady.

13:25.871 --> 13:27.372
If you remember,

13:27.373 --> 13:29.375
when I splashed Perry Miller,
he broke my nose.

13:33.379 --> 13:34.880
He did.

13:43.389 --> 13:44.389
Hi.

13:44.390 --> 13:46.891
Hi.

13:46.892 --> 13:49.394
Were you sitting there
watching me?

13:49.395 --> 13:51.896
Yeah, I guess.

13:51.897 --> 13:53.398
Oh, I look terrible.

13:53.399 --> 13:55.900
I look so awful in the morning.

13:55.901 --> 13:57.902
No, you don't.
You look pretty.

13:57.903 --> 13:59.404
No, I don't.

13:59.405 --> 14:01.406
Sure you do.
You look real pretty.

14:01.407 --> 14:02.907
You've got real pink cheeks,

14:02.908 --> 14:06.411
and your eyes are real sparkly.

14:06.412 --> 14:07.412
You look very pretty.

14:07.413 --> 14:09.414
Your breath
just smells a little.

14:09.415 --> 14:11.417
Oh...

14:15.921 --> 14:16.921
That's just because

14:16.922 --> 14:18.423
I haven't brushed my teeth.

14:18.424 --> 14:19.424
You know, listen.

14:19.425 --> 14:20.925
I'm sorry about last night.

14:20.926 --> 14:23.928
I'm really sorry.

14:23.929 --> 14:25.430
You're sorry?

14:25.431 --> 14:26.931
Yeah, I shouldn't have,
I really shouldn't have.

14:26.932 --> 14:28.433
I mean, I ain't got no business

14:28.434 --> 14:29.434
being with a girl like you.

14:29.435 --> 14:30.935
You're used to

14:30.936 --> 14:32.937
a whole different class of guy.

14:32.938 --> 14:34.439
It was the best ever,

14:34.440 --> 14:35.440
with you.

14:35.441 --> 14:36.941
Well, that's because

14:36.942 --> 14:38.943
you probably haven't been
with a guy before

14:38.944 --> 14:41.946
that hasn't seen a woman
in two years.

14:41.947 --> 14:43.448
Where are you going?

14:43.449 --> 14:44.449
Back to the basement.

14:44.450 --> 14:46.951
Oh, don't go.

14:46.952 --> 14:49.454
What do you want with me?

14:49.455 --> 14:50.455
I like you.

14:50.456 --> 14:51.456
Come on.

14:51.457 --> 14:52.457
I do.

14:52.458 --> 14:53.459
You like me?

14:54.960 --> 14:55.960
Get out of here.

14:55.961 --> 14:57.462
I do.

14:57.463 --> 15:00.465
Well, if you like me,
I guess I can't be all bad.

15:00.466 --> 15:01.467
You're not bad.

15:03.469 --> 15:04.969
Will I see you tonight?

15:04.970 --> 15:06.471
I don't think so.

15:06.472 --> 15:07.472
Why?

15:07.473 --> 15:11.476
Eunice, I'm wanted in 10 states.
10 states!

15:11.477 --> 15:13.478
I ain't got no future,

15:13.479 --> 15:14.979
and if I ain't got no future,

15:14.980 --> 15:17.482
I don't want you
to start being special to me.

15:19.485 --> 15:20.986
Am I special to you?

15:22.988 --> 15:24.990
Am I?

15:26.992 --> 15:28.493
Go brush your teeth.

15:32.498 --> 15:34.499
Well, Mary, tell me, what is it?

15:34.500 --> 15:36.501
I mean,
you sounded positively frantic

15:36.502 --> 15:37.502
over the phone.

15:37.503 --> 15:39.003
You won't believe it.

15:39.004 --> 15:42.507
You will absolutely not believe
what is going on in my life.

15:42.508 --> 15:44.008
This is big.

15:44.009 --> 15:45.009
Big?

15:45.010 --> 15:47.011
Oh, Mary,
you don't know what big is,

15:47.012 --> 15:48.012
because, of course,

15:48.013 --> 15:50.515
you don't know what's going on
in my life.

15:50.516 --> 15:52.016
What?

15:52.017 --> 15:54.018
That Corinne is
marrying a priest?

15:54.019 --> 15:55.019
Corinne?

15:55.020 --> 15:57.522
Oh, that is nothing.

15:57.523 --> 15:58.523
Well, what is it?

15:58.524 --> 16:00.024
No, Mary,

16:00.025 --> 16:02.026
you tell me yours first,

16:02.027 --> 16:06.531
because after I tell you mine,
you will not be able to talk.

16:06.532 --> 16:09.534
Okay, but put
your cup down first.

16:09.535 --> 16:11.036
Otherwise, you will
spill your tea.

16:13.539 --> 16:16.542
Jodie is going to be a father.

16:29.555 --> 16:31.557
Dennis is pregnant?

16:38.063 --> 16:41.065
No! Carol.

16:41.066 --> 16:43.568
Oh,

16:43.569 --> 16:47.573
because if it was Dennis,
you're right, that's big.

16:49.575 --> 16:52.577
He got a girl pregnant.

16:52.578 --> 16:55.079
My gay son
is going to be a father.

16:55.080 --> 16:57.582
That's your news?

16:59.084 --> 17:02.587
You don't think that's big news?

17:02.588 --> 17:04.088
No, that's news.

17:04.089 --> 17:06.089
I think that's news,

17:06.090 --> 17:08.593
not big news, but news.

17:11.096 --> 17:12.597
Not big news?

17:12.598 --> 17:15.098
Not compared to mine.

17:15.099 --> 17:16.601
Oh, really?

17:16.602 --> 17:18.102
Get ready, Mary.

17:18.103 --> 17:20.605
I'm ready, I'm ready.

17:20.606 --> 17:22.106
Mary,

17:22.107 --> 17:24.108
what do you think that I have

17:24.108 --> 17:25.609
in my basement?

17:27.613 --> 17:28.613
A thing.

17:28.614 --> 17:31.115
Your big news is about a thing?

17:31.116 --> 17:35.119
No, Mary, not a thing.

17:35.120 --> 17:37.122
Well, what is it?

17:38.624 --> 17:40.626
Two killers.

17:44.630 --> 17:48.132
Jessica,
what are you talking about?

17:48.133 --> 17:49.634
"Two killers."

17:49.635 --> 17:51.636
Two killers, Mary.

17:51.637 --> 17:54.639
I mean, I have two killers
in my basement.

17:54.640 --> 17:57.142
Who are they?

17:59.144 --> 18:03.147
Well, Chester is one of them,
but Dutch is the other one.

18:03.148 --> 18:04.649
You mean they came here?

18:04.650 --> 18:06.150
Yes, Mary, they're hiding out,

18:06.151 --> 18:08.152
and Dutch said
if we went for help,

18:08.153 --> 18:10.655
he'd kill us.

18:10.656 --> 18:12.156
You're kidding.
Uh-uh.

18:12.157 --> 18:13.157
Jessica, that's awful.

18:13.158 --> 18:16.661
You see, I told you.
Mine's bigger.

18:16.662 --> 18:20.665
Well, I don't know
if it's bigger, Jessica.

18:20.666 --> 18:21.666
It's awful...

18:23.669 --> 18:26.671
But I don't know if it's bigger.

18:26.672 --> 18:29.173
Two killers, Mary.

18:29.174 --> 18:30.675
I mean, I think two killers

18:30.676 --> 18:34.679
is bigger than a gay guy
and one pregnant girl.

18:34.680 --> 18:37.682
Yeah, I guess it's bigger.

18:37.683 --> 18:39.183
Although, yours is big.

18:39.184 --> 18:40.685
Of course it's big.

18:40.686 --> 18:43.188
It's just not bigger.

18:46.191 --> 18:48.693
I would have had you
if it had been Dennis.

18:59.204 --> 19:02.707
Ma, it's not your fault.

19:02.708 --> 19:04.709
Oh, Corinne, I'm sorry.

19:04.710 --> 19:05.710
I...I mean,

19:05.711 --> 19:08.212
I wanted to give you
a wonderful wedding,

19:08.213 --> 19:10.214
and now your very own father

19:10.215 --> 19:12.717
can't even be here.

19:12.718 --> 19:14.218
Ma, it's all right.

19:14.219 --> 19:15.219
I wonder,

19:15.220 --> 19:16.721
do you think it's too late

19:16.722 --> 19:19.724
to have the reception
down in the basement?

19:19.725 --> 19:20.725
Oh, Corinne,

19:20.726 --> 19:22.226
it's so hard to know what to do

19:22.227 --> 19:23.728
when there's an escaped prisoner

19:23.729 --> 19:25.229
in the family.

19:25.230 --> 19:26.230
Sorry.

19:27.733 --> 19:29.233
Ma,

19:29.234 --> 19:33.237
all I want is to marry Tim,

19:33.238 --> 19:36.741
and it's finally going
to come true.

19:36.742 --> 19:38.242
I'm happy, Ma,

19:38.243 --> 19:40.745
and if you gave me
the most elaborate,

19:40.746 --> 19:42.246
the fanciest wedding
in the whole world,

19:42.247 --> 19:44.249
it couldn't make me any happier.

19:46.251 --> 19:48.252
Oh, I love you, Corinne.

19:48.253 --> 19:49.253
I love you.

19:49.254 --> 19:50.254
I love you too, Ma.

19:50.255 --> 19:52.257
I know.

19:55.260 --> 19:56.761
I'll wave to you.

19:56.762 --> 19:58.262
Okay.

19:58.263 --> 20:01.265
[ORGAN MUSIC BEGINS]

20:01.266 --> 20:02.266
Well, you're about ready?

20:02.267 --> 20:03.768
Yeah.

20:03.769 --> 20:06.771
How does it feel
to break your word?

20:06.772 --> 20:07.772
What?

20:07.773 --> 20:09.774
Don't your remember?

20:09.775 --> 20:11.776
You told me
when you were 9 years old

20:11.777 --> 20:14.278
that you'd never get married,
not in a million years.

20:14.279 --> 20:16.781
Did I really say that?

20:16.782 --> 20:18.282
Yeah.

20:18.283 --> 20:21.786
It was all on account of a fight
you'd had with Tommy Gibbs.

20:21.787 --> 20:23.287
You and he
had made some lemonade,

20:23.288 --> 20:25.289
and when the fight started,

20:25.290 --> 20:27.291
he ran home,
and you gave me his share,

20:27.292 --> 20:30.294
but what I remember most
about it was...

20:30.295 --> 20:34.298
we sat on the porch
and drank lemonade,

20:34.299 --> 20:35.800
and you called me
your best friend.

20:37.803 --> 20:41.305
Oh, Benson... You are.

20:41.306 --> 20:42.807
You really are.

20:45.310 --> 20:48.312
Oh, my gosh.

20:48.313 --> 20:50.815
Who is that?

20:50.816 --> 20:53.818
That's Mrs. Flotsky.
That's Tim's mother.

20:53.819 --> 20:55.820
We never thought
she'd come to the wedding.

20:55.821 --> 20:58.322
This is wonderful.
Tim will be so happy.

20:58.323 --> 21:01.326
[ORGAN MUSIC TEMPO QUICKENS]

21:04.830 --> 21:06.330
Father Tim, what
are you doing here?

21:06.331 --> 21:09.333
I'm getting married.
Didn't you know, Father?

21:09.334 --> 21:13.338
You mean priests can marry now?

21:15.340 --> 21:17.341
No, Father,
I'm no longer a priest.

21:17.342 --> 21:21.846
Oh. I thought
it seemed too good to be true.

21:24.349 --> 21:26.851
[WEDDING MARCH PLAYING]

21:49.374 --> 21:52.376
And now,
if the father of the bride

21:52.377 --> 21:55.379
could please take his place

21:55.380 --> 21:56.881
with the other guests...

21:56.882 --> 21:57.882
Excuse me.

21:57.883 --> 21:58.883
[WHISPERS]

21:58.884 --> 22:01.385
Oh, will the best friend
of the bride

22:01.386 --> 22:03.888
please take his place
with the other guests,

22:03.889 --> 22:04.890
yes.

22:10.896 --> 22:13.397
Dearly beloved,

22:13.398 --> 22:15.399
we are gathered here
in the sight of God

22:15.400 --> 22:17.401
to join this man and this woman

22:17.402 --> 22:18.402
in holy matrimony.

22:18.403 --> 22:21.405
If any person
can show just cause

22:21.406 --> 22:24.408
why they may not
lawfully be joined together,

22:24.409 --> 22:26.410
let him now declare it

22:26.411 --> 22:29.413
or forever hold his peace.

22:29.414 --> 22:30.915
And now, if the groom...

22:30.916 --> 22:33.417
"Just cause?!"
I'll give you just cause.

22:33.418 --> 22:36.420
What right does that bimbo have
to take my son's life

22:36.421 --> 22:37.922
and turn it into garbage?

22:37.923 --> 22:40.424
Oh,
you could have been a bishop,

22:40.425 --> 22:41.425
at least, by now,

22:41.426 --> 22:42.927
if it weren't for this tramp,

22:42.928 --> 22:43.928
or maybe even a cardinal.

22:43.929 --> 22:44.929
Ma...

22:44.930 --> 22:46.430
There should be laws
against you.

22:46.431 --> 22:48.933
You're a terrible,
terrible person.

22:48.934 --> 22:50.936
Yes you are. Terrible!

22:53.939 --> 22:55.440
There be no just cause.

22:57.943 --> 22:59.945
Let us proceed.

23:01.446 --> 23:03.447
Tim...

23:03.448 --> 23:05.950
do you take Corinne,
here present,

23:05.951 --> 23:07.451
to be your lawful wife

23:07.452 --> 23:08.953
according to the right

23:08.954 --> 23:10.955
of the holy church of God?

23:10.956 --> 23:12.457
I do, Father.

23:14.960 --> 23:16.962
[♪]

23:22.467 --> 23:23.968
<i>Will Danny and Elaine</i>

23:23.969 --> 23:25.469
<i>ever have a relationship</i>
<i>that works?</i>

23:25.470 --> 23:26.971
<i>Will Chuck</i>
<i>ever have a relationship</i>

23:26.972 --> 23:28.472
<i>with Bob around?</i>

23:28.473 --> 23:31.475
<i>What will be left</i>
<i>of Burt and Mary's relationship</i>

23:31.476 --> 23:33.978
<i>living with Danny and Elaine</i>
<i>and Chuck and Bob?</i>

23:33.979 --> 23:35.479
<i>What kind of a relationship</i>

23:35.480 --> 23:37.481
<i>could Eunice and Dutch</i>
<i>ever have?</i>

23:37.482 --> 23:39.483
<i>Will Tim's relationship</i>
<i>with his mother</i>

23:39.484 --> 23:41.986
<i>destroy his relationship</i>
<i>with Corinne?</i>

23:41.987 --> 23:44.989
<i>What kind of relationship</i>
<i>can Chester and Jessica have</i>

23:44.990 --> 23:46.490
<i>with Chester</i>
<i>living in the basement</i>

23:46.491 --> 23:48.492
<i>and Jessica living upstairs?</i>

23:48.493 --> 23:50.995
<i>These questions and many others</i>
<i>will be answered</i>

23:50.996 --> 23:52.497
<i>on next's week episode of...</i>

